DIGEST
SB 129 Original 2026 Regular Session Foil
Proposed law creates the "Master Combat Infantryman" special prestige license plate.
Proposed law requires the secretary of the Dept. of Public Safety and Corrections to issue
the "Master Combat Infantryman" special prestige license plate.
Proposed law provides that the office of motor vehicles shall create the plate when their
electronic vehicle and title registration system is updated.
Proposed law provides each military honor license plate issued shall be returned to the
secretary upon the death of the person to whom the plate was issued. Proposed law further
provides the surviving spouse of a person to whom the plate was issued may retain the
license plate provided the surviving spouse has not remarried and applies to the secretary for
a transfer of the license plate.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 47:463.243)
